  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for tracker-miners",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for tracker-miners fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2026-1764: heap buffer overflow leads to denial of service or information disclosure when parsing MP3 files\n  (bsc#1257606).\n- CVE-2026-1765: denial of Service and potential information disclosure via crafted MP3 files (bsc#1257607).\n- CVE-2026-1766: denial of Service and information disclosure via malformed MP3 files (bsc#1257608).\n- CVE-2026-1767: heap buffer overflow leading to denial of service or information disclosure via malformed MP3 ID3\n  tags (bsc#1257609).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
